{"key":"post-5753090","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5753090</id>\n<content>Pelletized lime is 100% useless for mycology. It's intended to break down in your lawn over a period of months to even years.  The average life of a casing layer is three to four weeks, so the pelletized stuff won't do squat.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Mix hydrated &lt;i&gt;garden&lt;/i&gt; lime to your dry peat at the rate of one teaspoon per cup of peat.  That should give you a great starting point.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5753603</next>\n<prev>5753071</prev>\n<first>5749885</first>\n<last>5760272</last>\n<when>1150390033</when>\n<utime>06/15/06 07:47 PM</utime>\n</post>"}